ich is what happens when there is too much tamas and rajas. There a=\r\nre many self-styled &quot;Hindutva&quot; warriors today who fall in the latter catego=\r\nry. They yell from rooftops in shrill voices, but do not accomplish much. D=\r\no we need some more such people?\n \n*        *        *\n \nWhat Hindutva need=\r\ns today is a few detached Arjunas who destroy mighty armies without hatred =\r\nfor anyone in their heart. What Hindutva needs today is a few detached Vive=\r\nkanandas who inspire millions with their magnetic personality without any p=\r\nassion in their heart.\n \nAct like a passionate man, but have no passion in =\r\nyour heart. Fight unwaveringly, but have no hatred for anyone.\n \nIf one is =\r\nfighting a war with passion, frustration or hatred in one&#39;s heart, one will=\r\n only go so far and achieve only so much. What such a person achieves will =\r\nbe short-lived. If one first overcomes attractions and repulsions, has a st=\r\nable and unperturbed heart without passion and hatred and becomes a detache=\r\nd instrument of Nature engaging in spontaneous actions without any attachme=\r\nnt, one will achieve much more and what one achieves will be long-lived.\n \n=\r\nI am writing this to this group of people because my intuition tells me tha=\r\nt there are some on this group who have the potential to become such instru=\r\nments of Mother.\n \nDo some spiritual sadhana first and overcome the weaknes=\r\nses. Have a stable, unperturbed and equanimous heart. Then Nature will show=\r\n you the way.\n \n*        *        *\n \nCeturies ago, western invaders went a=\r\nbout their business with great dexterity and patience to affect the psyche =\r\nof Hindus, especially intelligentsia. Their slow, patient, dexterous and sy=\r\nstematic propaganda is bearing fruit even today. To undo their work, one ne=\r\neds to be equally dexterous and patient. This is not the work for hot-blood=\r\ned, angry and frustrated people. One needs to be cool-headed, smart and pat=\r\nient.\n \nAnother thing is that sanatana dharma is broken today. In pursuit o=\r\nf modern education, the cream of Indian intelligentsia stopped engaging in =\r\nour traditional knowledge. This brought a discontinuity in knowledge. We ha=\r\nve some faithful Hindus engaging in superstitious and/or purposeless practi=\r\nces. We have many priests who are corrupted by money and fame, don&#39;t do any=\r\n sadhana and don&#39;t have any spiritual strength. Many intelligent people eit=\r\nher dissociate themselves from religion or follow religion passively withou=\r\nt much faith and with some shame or misgivings. At the root of this is the =\r\nbroken knowledge and purposeless practices.\n \nAlso, we have many bad practi=\r\nces that afflict Hinduism due to Kali, which need to be gotten rid of. For =\r\nexample, caste system of today is so different from old days. The concept o=\r\nf caste mobility is gone now - one would start with father&#39;s caste, but get=\r\n a caste later on based on one&#39;s aptitude and attitude in old days. For exa=\r\nmple, Valmiki was a shudra by birth who lived by killing birds and he becam=\r\ne a brahmana and a brahmarshi later. Vishwamitra was a kshatriya by birth b=\r\nut became a brahmana and a brahmarshi later and even became one of saptarsh=\r\nis. If lower caste and untouchable Hindus feel aversion to Hinduism which i=\r\ns exploted by Christian missionaries who offer money and respect to convert=\r\n, some fault lies with Hinduism too. We need to reform casteism.\n \nThere ar=\r\ne many things that need to be done. At one level, some propaganda needs to =\r\nbe done on the greatness of Hinduism. This needs to be done with a cool, sc=\r\nholarly and patient attitude (as opposed to yelling in shrill voice from ro=\r\noftops like some Hindutva activists foolishly do). At another level, broken=\r\n links within Hinduism need to be rediscovered so that the knowledgebase of=\r\n our philosophy is correctly represented to sway the intelligentsia. While =\r\nother religions are based on &quot;faith&quot; in the words of a messiah, Hinduism ha=\r\ns a wide-ranging and sophisticated philosophy and methods that can enable a=\r\nnyone to become a messiah. However, the knowledge has become corrupted and =\r\nincomplete and some intelligent people are justified in not having faith. A=\r\nt yet another level, we need to reform some social and cultural aspects of =\r\nHindusm and undo some changes brought in by Kali.\n \nThere are many things t=\r\no do and this will take many decades of focused and concerted effort.\n \n*  =\r\n      *        *\n \nPersonally, I have no doubt that the time of weakening (=\r\nor even fall) of certain faiths has come. In the next few decades, some fai=\r\nths will be weakened considerably and sanatana dharma will be strengthened.=\r\n However, this being Kali yuga, such a change will not be permanent.\n \nBest=\r\n regards,\nNarasimha\n-------------------------------------------------------=\r\n-----------\nDo a Short Homam Yourself: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org/homam=\r\n\nDo Pitri Tarpanas Yourself: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org/tarpana\nSpiritu=\r\nality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom\nFree Jyotish lessons (MP3=\r\n): http://vedicastro.home.comcast.net\nFree Jyotish software (Windows): http=\r\n://www.VedicAstrologer.org\nSri Jagannath Centre (SJC) website: http://www.S=\r\nriJagannath.org\n-----------------------------------------------------------=\r\n-------\n \n--- On Tue, 3/31/09, Rahul Chaturvedi &lt;rahul@...=\r\n&gt; wrote:\n  From: Rahul Chaturvedi &lt;rahul@...&gt;\n  Subject: R=\r\ne: Conversion-God&#39;s work -Sr Mary Prema Superior of the MoC\n  To: &quot;swamisat=\r\nhasivom sri&quot; &lt;swamisathasivom@...&gt;\n  Cc: &quot;Amba Sarah Caldwell&quot; &lt;aumsa=\r\nthyojathamba5@...&gt;, &quot;pecchennai&quot; &lt;admin@...&gt;, &quot;Shiva Mani&quot;=\r\n &lt;asivamani@...&gt;, &quot;appu rai&quot; &lt;drpedocare_rai@..