&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;Namaste=\r\n Rahul and others,&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FO=\r\nNT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;We all have some fire within us.=\r\n When we channel \nit&nbsp;properly, we fulfil our dharma successfully. When=\r\n the fire is \nunchanneled and&nbsp;beset with impurities, we waste energy a=\r\nnd fail to fulfil \nour dharma.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D=\r\n2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;Fire&nbsp;in conjunc=\r\ntion with sattwa guna generates \nknowledge (jnaana shakti).&nbsp;Fire&nbsp;=\r\nin conjunction with rajo guna \ngenerates actions (kriyaa shakti).&nbsp;Fire=\r\n&nbsp;in conjunction with tamo guna \ngenerates desires (ichchhaa shakti). W=\r\ne need people who&nbsp;mainly have sattwa \nand also some rajas. Such people=\r\n have clear thinking&nbsp;backed by correct \nknowledge and engage in fruitf=\r\nul actions. It is more important to engage in a \nfew fruitful actions than =\r\nto engage in too many mis-directed actions and be left \nwith unfulfilled de=\r\nsires and frustration, which is what happens when there is \ntoo much tamas =\r\nand rajas. There are many self-styled &quot;Hindutva&quot; warriors today \nwho fall i=\r\nn the latter category. They yell from rooftops in shrill voices, but \ndo no=\r\nt accomplish much. Do we need some more such people?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FON=\r\nT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial s=\r\nize=3D2&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp=\r\n;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;What Hindutva&nbsp;ne=\r\neds today is a few detached \nArjunas who destroy mighty armies without hatr=\r\ned for anyone in their heart. What \nHindutva needs today is a few detached =\r\nVivekanandas who inspire millions with \ntheir magnetic personality without =\r\nany passion in their heart.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&=\r\nnbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;Act like a passionate m=\r\nan, but have no passion in \nyour heart. Fight unwaveringly, but have no hat=\r\nred for anyone.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;=\r\n&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;If one is fighting a war with passi=\r\non, \nfrustration&nbsp;or hatred in one&#39;s heart, one will only go so far and=\r\n achieve \nonly so much. What such a person achieves will be short-lived. If=\r\n one first \novercomes attractions and repulsions, has a stable and unpertur=\r\nbed \nheart&nbsp;without passion and hatred and becomes a detached instrumen=\r\nt of \nNature engaging in spontaneous actions without any attachment, one wi=\r\nll achieve \nmuch more and what one achieves will be long-lived.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV=\r\n&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DAr=\r\nial size=3D2&gt;I am writing this to this group of people because \nmy intuitio=\r\nn tells me that there are some on this group who have the potential \nto bec=\r\nome such instruments of Mother.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=\r\n=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;Do some spiritual=\r\n sadhana first and overcome the \nweaknesses. Have a stable, unperturbed and=\r\n equanimous heart. Then Nature will \nshow you the way.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;F=\r\nONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=\r\n=3D2&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/=\r\nFONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;Ceturies ago, western invaders=\r\n went about their \nbusiness with great dexterity and patience to affect the=\r\n psyche of Hindus, \nespecially intelligentsia. Their slow, patient, dextero=\r\nus&nbsp;and systematic \npropaganda is bearing fruit even today. To undo the=\r\nir work, one needs to be \nequally dexterous and patient. This is not the wo=\r\nrk for hot-blooded, angry and \nfrustrated people. One needs to be cool-head=\r\ned, smart and patient.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;=\r\n&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;Another thing is that sanata=\r\nna dharma is broken \ntoday. In pursuit of modern education, the cream of In=\r\ndian intelligentsia \nstopped engaging in our traditional knowledge. This br=\r\nought a discontinuity in \nknowledge. We have some faithful Hindus engaging =\r\nin superstitious and/or \npurposeless practices. We have many priests who ar=\r\ne corrupted by money and fame, \ndon&#39;t do any sadhana and don&#39;t have any spi=\r\nritual strength. Many intelligent \npeople either dissociate themselves from=\r\n religion or follow religion passively \nwithout much faith and with some sh=\r\name or misgivings. At the root of this is the \nbroken knowledge and purpose=\r\nless practices.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;=\r\n&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;Also, we have many bad practices th=\r\nat afflict \nHinduism due to Kali, which need to be gotten rid of. For examp=\r\nle, caste system \nof today is so different from old days. The concept of ca=\r\nste mobility is gone \nnow&nbsp;- one would start with father&#39;s caste, but g=\r\net a caste later on based \non one&#39;s aptitude and attitude in old days. For =\r\nexample, Valmiki was a shudra by \nbirth who lived by killing birds and he b=\r\necame a brahmana and a brahmarshi \nlater. Vishwamitra was a kshatriya by bi=\r\nrth but became a brahmana and a \nbrahmarshi later and even became one of sa=\r\nptarshis. If lower caste and \nuntouchable Hindus&nbsp;feel aversion to Hind=\r\nuism which is exploted by Christian \nmissionaries who offer money and respe=\r\nct to convert, &lt;EM&gt;some&lt;/EM&gt; fault lies \nwith Hinduism too. We need to refo=\r\nrm casteism.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/D=\r\nIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;There are many things that need to be =\r\ndone. At one \nlevel, some propaganda needs to be done on the greatness of H=\r\ninduism. This needs \nto be done with a cool, scholarly&nbsp;and patient att=\r\nitude (as opposed to \nyelling in shrill voice from rooftops like some Hindu=\r\ntva activists foolishly \ndo). At another level, broken links within Hinduis=\r\nm need to be rediscovered so \nthat the knowledgebase of our philosophy is c=\r\norrectly represented to sway the \nintelligentsia. While other religions are=\r\n based on &quot;faith&quot; in the words of a \nmessiah, Hinduism has a wide-ranging a=\r\nnd sophisticated philosophy and methods \nthat can enable &lt;EM&gt;anyone &lt;/EM&gt;to=\r\n &lt;EM&gt;become&lt;/EM&gt; a messiah. However, the \nknowledge has become corrupted an=\r\nd incomplete and some intelligent people are \njustified in not having&nbsp;=\r\nfaith. At yet another level, we need to reform some \nsocial and cultural as=\r\npects of Hindusm and undo some changes brought in by \nKali.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;D=\r\nIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial =\r\nsize=3D2&gt;There are many things to do and this will take many \ndecades of fo=\r\ncused and concerted effort.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&=\r\nnbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=\r\np;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;=\r\n/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=\r\n=3DArial size=3D2&gt;Personally, I have no doubt that the time of \nweakening (=\r\nor even fall)&nbsp;of certain faiths has come. In the next few \ndecades, so=\r\nme faiths will be weakened considerably and sanatana dharma will be \nstreng=\r\nthened. However, this being Kali yuga, such a change will not be \npermanent=\r\n.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;F=\r\nONT face=3DArial size=3D2&gt;Best \nregards,&lt;BR&gt;Narasimha&lt;BR&gt;------------------=\r\n------------------------------------------------&lt;BR&gt;Do \na Short Homam Yours=\r\nelf: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org/homam&lt;BR&gt;Do Pitri \nTarpanas Yourself: h=\r\nttp://www.VedicAstrologer.org/tarpana&lt;BR&gt;Spirituality: \nhttp://groups.yahoo=\r\n.com/group/vedic-wisdom&lt;BR&gt;Free Jyotish lessons (MP3): \nhttp://vedicastro.h=\r\nome.comcast.net&lt;BR&gt;Free Jyotish software (Windows): \nhttp://www.VedicAstrol=\r\noger.org&lt;BR&gt;Sri Jagannath Centre (SJC) website: \nhttp://www.SriJagannath.or=\r\ng&lt;BR&gt;------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;BR&gt;=\r\n&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;--- \nOn &lt;B&gt;Tue, 3/31/09, Rahul Chaturvedi \n&lt;I&gt;&lt;rahul@to=\r\ntalcarenetwork.com&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt; wrote:&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;BLOCKQUOTE \nstyle=3D&quot;PADDING-L=\r\nEFT: 5px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px; BORDER-LEFT: rgb(16,16,255) 2px solid&quot;&gt;From: \n =\r\n Rahul Chaturvedi &lt;rahul@...&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Subject: Re: \n  Con=\r\nversion-God&#39;s work -Sr Ma